Privacy Policy for Amazon Time Tracker
Last Updated: October 18, 2025
Overview
Amazon Time Tracker is committed to protecting your privacy. This extension operates with complete transparency and respects your data.
Data Collection
Amazon Time Tracker collects and stores the following information locally on your device:

Time spent on Amazon websites
Timestamps of browsing sessions
Date of each session

Data Storage

All data is stored locally in your browser using Chrome's storage API
No data is transmitted to external servers
No data is shared with third parties
No personal information is collected or stored
No browsing history or URLs are recorded beyond Amazon domains

Data Usage
The collected data is used solely for:

Displaying your Amazon browsing time in the extension popup
Generating session history and daily summaries
Providing you with insights into your browsing habits

Data Retention

Data older than 30 days is automatically deleted
You can manually clear all data at any time using the "Clear All History" button
Uninstalling the extension permanently removes all stored data

Third-Party Services

This extension does not use any third-party analytics services
This extension does not use any tracking cookies
This extension does not communicate with external servers

Affiliate Disclosure
This extension may add an affiliate tag to Amazon product links. This allows the extension developer to earn a small commission from Amazon on qualifying purchases at no additional cost to you. This does not affect the price you pay or the products you see.
Permissions
The extension requires the following permissions:

Storage: To save your browsing time data locally
Host Permissions (Amazon domains): To detect when you're on Amazon and track time accordingly

Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access your data through the extension interface
Delete your data at any time
Uninstall the extension to permanently remove all data

Changes to This Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the "Last Updated" date above.
Contact
If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us through the Chrome Web Store support page.
Consent
By installing and using Amazon Time Tracker, you consent to this privacy policy.
